      {
        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "Short answer: “the” binding constant for DTPA isn’t a single number — it depends on which metal ion (and on pH, ionic strength, temperature, and the exact species/stoichiometry reported). In SRD‑46, DTPA (ligand_6356; diethylenetriaminepentaacetic acid) has measured formation constants (logβ/logK) for many metals near room temperature in aqueous media. Tell me the metal and I’ll return the exact logβ1 for the ML (1:1) species with conditions and a citation.",
